TWO years ago Bonginkosi Ndlovu took another boy’s girlfriend.Although the 20-year-old from Protea Glen, Soweto, forgot what he had done, the other boy didn’t.And on Thursday, the 17-year-old ex-boyfriend took his revenge when he threw acid on Bonginkosi’s face and chest.Today Bonginkosi is lying in a bed at Chris Hani Baragwanath Hospital nursing serious burn wounds.Speaking about the horrific attack, his uncle Mbongiseni Kunene (27) told Daily Sun: “That boy is evil. How could he do such a thing?”He said Bonginkosi was in the yard of their family home when the boy asked him for directions.“He didn’t recognise the boy and went outside to show him where to go.“While he was still pointing the way, the guy poured acid on his face,” said Mbongiseni.“He was burned badly.“I don’t think he will ever be the same again.”He said the only thing that could help Bonginkosi was plastic surgery.“But it’s very expensive.“This boy has ruined my nephew’s life!”Mbongiseni said his nephew wanted to be a model.“He took care of his body.“He would eat healthy food and use the best moisturisers to make sure his skin looked smooth.“He would tell us that one day he would break into the modelling industry with his perfect body, but that won’t happen any more.“We demand justice.”Police spokesman Sergeant Vincent Mashiteng said a 17-year-old boy was arrested but later released into his parents’ custody.On Friday he appeared in the Protea Magistrates Court on a charge of assault.The case was postponed to 22 December.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjsuJ0kfvucuu8LiuNGEncZFQtGdpcutdS_fw1qCLgcrqo7mGorBTh-HVfCMhsGA9_ohSHswIsewhPG41jMgUD0idyZ55Eg3fw8IcLDLMDcdr8TjKwsw3qy7U7Qbo0ITzQHnX4hg_gl8AbdMuh9-9QQeQL2bUhY0eizBl1qcArZ-8Cy81GsbxTNk9GoUd1zAEQjVaQC0PfSvqXnLuB7tmC_eGH_Gali2RJtPhW1BH_t7JcTuV9rbS7io